.nh
.TH "SYMAIRA" "1" "May 2026" "Symaira Vault" "OpenPass Manual"

.SH NAME
symaira-mcp-install - Auto-configure an AI agent to use the OpenPass MCP server


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBsymaira mcp install [agent] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Automatically detect and configure a supported AI agent to use the OpenPass MCP server.

.PP
Supported agents:
  - openclaw    (OpenClaw)
  - claude-code (Claude Code)
  - hermes      (Hermes)
  - codex       (OpenAI Codex CLI)
  - opencode    (OpenCode)

.PP
The command detects if the agent is installed, finds its MCP config file,
and injects the OpenPass server configuration. When using HTTP mode, a
scoped token is automatically generated for the agent.

.PP
The operation is idempotent: running it multiple times will not create
duplicate entries.

.PP
Examples:
  openpass mcp install openclaw
  openpass mcp install claude-code --http
  openpass mcp install --auto-detect
  openpass mcp install hermes --dry-run


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--auto-detect\fP[=false]
	Detect all installed agents and configure them

.PP
\fB--dry-run\fP[=false]
	Preview changes without applying them

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for install

.PP
\fB--http\fP[=false]
	Use HTTP transport with auto-generated bearer token

.PP
\fB--stdio\fP[=true]
	Use stdio transport (default)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--color\fP="auto"
	When to emit ANSI color: auto, always, never

.PP
\fB--no-pipe-warning\fP[=false]
	suppress 'reading from non-TTY' warning when piping secrets

.PP
\fB--output\fP="text"
	Output format (text, json, yaml)

.PP
\fB--profile\fP=""
	use a named vault profile

.PP
\fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	suppress non-error output

.PP
\fB--theme\fP=""
	Color preset: default, highcontrast, colorblind (or OPENPASS_THEME)

.PP
\fB--vault\fP="~/.openpass"
	path to the password vault


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Install MCP integration for Claude Code (auto-detected)
  openpass mcp install claude-code

  # HTTP mode with a fresh scoped token
  openpass mcp install claude-code --http

  # List installed agent integrations
  openpass mcp install --list
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBsymaira-mcp(1)\fP
